# Copy to `frontend/.env.local` (same folder). Vite loads it automatically; never commit `.env.local`.
#
# Run only the React app on localhost; the API runs on AWS (ECS Fargate).
# Set this to the public IP (or hostname) of a running API task, port 3001.
#
# Find the IP: AWS Console → ECS → Clusters → cardboardforge-prod-cluster →
# Services → cardboardforge-prod-api → Tasks (running) → click task →
# "Public IP" under Configuration.
#
# No trailing slash. Example (remote API only — not needed for `pnpm dev:local`):
# VITE_API_URL=http://54.123.45.67:3001
#
# For local dev, omit VITE_API_URL entirely so requests stay same-origin and Vite proxies `/api` → localhost:3001.
# A placeholder hostname here will break auth (ERR_NAME_NOT_RESOLVED).

# Google Sign-In (OAuth 2.0 Client ID, type “Web application”). Required for “Continue with Google”.
# In Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials: add Authorized JavaScript origins
# (e.g. http://localhost:5173 and your production site origin). Optional locally if you only use email/password.
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=123456789-xxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
